# ui

Renders a user interface surface contract — a screen, page, view, or component. Like a function contract, a ui block uses fixed sub-headers that each define a specific element type. Only the elements declared inside are built; the model is forbidden from adding or omitting any.

# entity Input

- directive: 'ui'
- name: the surface name (e.g. 'LoginScreen', 'OrderTable', 'ProfileCard') — optional
- body: raw sub-block content containing ## form, ## block, ## image, and ## table headers

# entity SubBlock

The compiler splits the body on `## ` prefixed lines to extract these before rendering. Multiple sub-blocks of the same kind are valid — each renders as its own section.

- kind: 'form' | 'block' | 'image' | 'table'
  which sub-header this came from
- label: string | undefined
  the optional name on the sub-header line (e.g. `loginForm` from `## form loginForm`)
- content: string
  everything written under this sub-header, trimmed

# entity Output

```markdown
### UI SURFACE{{#name}}: {{name}}{{/name}}

Build this user interface surface exactly as specified. Implement only the elements declared below — do not add components, fields, columns, controls, or decorative elements that are not listed, and do not omit any that are. Match the structure, labels, validation, and behavior described for each element.

{{body}}

{{forms}}

{{blocks}}

{{images}}

{{tables}}
```

# rule

- name is optional. When present the header is `### UI SURFACE: {{name}}`; when absent it is `### UI SURFACE` with no colon or name.
- The compiler splits the body on `## ` prefixed lines: everything before the first sub-header becomes `{{body}}`; the rest becomes the typed sub-blocks.
- {{forms}} expands to one section per `## form` sub-block:
  `#### FORM{{#label}}: {{label}}{{/label}}\n\nRender this form with exactly the fields and actions listed — no extra inputs, no omitted ones. Apply the stated validation rules and wire each action to its described behavior:\n\n{{content}}`
- {{blocks}} expands to one section per `## block` sub-block:
  `#### BLOCK{{#label}}: {{label}}{{/label}}\n\nCompose this visual region exactly as described. Do not introduce additional sections or rearrange the declared structure:\n\n{{content}}`
- {{images}} expands to one section per `## image` sub-block:
  `#### IMAGE{{#label}}: {{label}}{{/label}}\n\nPlace this image as specified, honoring its source, alt text, and role in the layout. Do not substitute it or add imagery beyond what is declared:\n\n{{content}}`
- {{tables}} expands to one section per `## table` sub-block:
  `#### TABLE{{#label}}: {{label}}{{/label}}\n\nRender this table with exactly the columns and data binding described. Implement the stated sorting, pagination, and empty-state behavior; do not add columns that are not listed:\n\n{{content}}`
- When a sub-block kind has no entries, its placeholder is omitted entirely — do not render an empty section.
- Sub-block labels are optional. When absent, render `#### FORM` / `#### BLOCK` / `#### IMAGE` / `#### TABLE` with no colon or name suffix.
- When `{{body}}` is empty (no intro text before the first sub-header), omit the blank line placeholder.
- {variable} references in sub-block content and body are resolved against the reads map before sub-block extraction.
